474
00:33:21,728 --> 00:33:25,220
You think if you come in late and spit
on the boss that will get you fired?

475
00:33:25,398 --> 00:33:27,127
Not in this company.

476
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:29,632
- Chris.
- George.

477
00:33:32,939 --> 00:33:34,566
George, I have an ulcer.

478
00:33:34,741 --> 00:33:37,733
I don't sleep well, mostly because
you keep calling me at night.

479
00:33:37,910 --> 00:33:40,242
If you don't call me,
I dream you're gonna call me.

480
00:33:40,413 --> 00:33:43,246
I think about you in the shower,
not in a good way...

481
00:33:43,416 --> 00:33:46,749
...but in an I'm-so-distracted-I-can't-
remember-if-I washed-my-hair way.

482
00:33:46,919 --> 00:33:48,750
So I wash my hair twice.

483
00:33:48,921 --> 00:33:52,049
So I have a hole in my stomach,
I am running out of shampoo...

484
00:33:52,225 --> 00:33:56,093
...and today is the first time in my life
I did not give a 1000 percent on the job...

485
00:33:56,262 --> 00:33:58,924
...and I hate that feeling!

486
00:34:04,437 --> 00:34:08,737
- I won't call after hours.
- You will, George! You know you will.

487
00:34:09,442 --> 00:34:10,841
Yeah, I will.

488
00:34:12,178 --> 00:34:17,946
I just don't think we can see each other
professionally anymore.

489
00:34:26,959 --> 00:34:29,427
All right. Stay until you find
a replacement.

490
00:34:29,595 --> 00:34:32,860
Train him up for a couple of weeks,
then you can go to Slurpee Heaven.

491
00:34:33,533 --> 00:34:36,798
Thank you! I promise I will find
you somebody amazing.

492
00:34:36,969 --> 00:34:39,631
Somebody better than me
because I'm not even any good.

493
00:34:39,806 --> 00:34:43,037
- No.
- A glorified ambulance chaser.

494
00:34:45,044 --> 00:34:46,875
Thank you.

495
00:34:59,492 --> 00:35:02,052
I got it. It's just my earring.

496
00:35:04,063 --> 00:35:06,657
- My hair!
- Careful! That's my overpriced Italian belt.

497
00:35:06,833 --> 00:35:09,631
Just get it off!

498
00:35:10,403 --> 00:35:12,337
Howard.

499
00:35:12,839 --> 00:35:15,672
Join us. We were just brainstorming.

500
00:35:16,409 --> 00:35:18,240
- Lucy?
- Yes.

501
00:35:18,411 --> 00:35:23,348
I was thinking it might be a good idea
to do a photo op at the build site...

502
00:35:23,516 --> 00:35:26,349
...where George would be in the...

503
00:35:26,919 --> 00:35:30,150
George in the foreground,
pointing up to the sky...

504
00:35:30,323 --> 00:35:31,915
...like this.
- Yes.

505
00:35:32,091 --> 00:35:37,085
Then I thought I could take my belt off,
as if to say, let's get to work!

506
00:35:37,263 --> 00:35:40,198
Right. Right-o.

507
00:35:40,767 --> 00:35:44,032
On behalf of Wade Corporation,
I'd like to thank the Community Board...

508
00:35:44,203 --> 00:35:47,229
...for giving us the opportunity
to work with you on this project.

509
00:35:47,406 --> 00:35:50,603
And we look forward to seeing
all of you at the groundbreaking.

510
00:35:51,077 --> 00:35:52,704
I did well with those eight people.

511
00:35:52,879 --> 00:35:55,347
- I thought you were fantastic.
- This way, Mr. Wade.

512
00:35:55,515 --> 00:35:56,641
Just Mr. Wade.

513
00:35:57,216 --> 00:35:59,946
- More.
- Great. Can we go now?

514
00:36:00,119 --> 00:36:02,952
Absolutely. I just want to say hello
to my folks.

515
00:36:03,122 --> 00:36:04,111
Folks?

516
00:36:04,457 --> 00:36:06,288
Excuse me.

517
00:36:06,993 --> 00:36:08,119
Hello.

518
00:36:08,294 --> 00:36:09,352
- Hi, honey.
- Hi, Daddy.

519
00:36:09,529 --> 00:36:11,326
- Is that a new coat? I like it.
- Thanks.

520
00:36:11,497 --> 00:36:16,161
What a wonderful surprise!
We finally meet after all this time.

521
00:36:16,335 --> 00:36:17,632
George Wade.

522
00:36:17,804 --> 00:36:19,965
Mrs. Kelson, I presume.

523
00:36:20,139 --> 00:36:21,197
What a pleasure.

524
00:36:26,579 --> 00:36:31,642
Well, I can certainly see
where Lucy gets her stare from.

525
00:36:31,818 --> 00:36:33,752
I'm Larry. It's a pleasure to meet you.

526
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:35,979
Thanks, Larry. Same here.

527
00:36:36,155 --> 00:36:38,988
Thank you for letting Lucy quit.
It certainly made our week.

528
00:36:39,158 --> 00:36:41,820
- Great pleasure.
- We should get back to the office.

529
00:36:41,994 --> 00:36:43,928
- Come on! Have some cake.
- We can't.

530
00:36:44,096 --> 00:36:46,326
We're two blocks from the apartment.

531
00:36:46,499 --> 00:36:47,796
- You live around here?
- Sure.

532
00:36:47,967 --> 00:36:50,435
- What a charming coincidence.
- It won't be charming...

533
00:36:50,603 --> 00:36:55,267
...once you block out the sun
with this condo-hotel monstrosity!

534
00:36:56,509 --> 00:36:59,103
We will have a sun deck.

535
00:37:00,847 --> 00:37:03,042
That's something, isn't it?

536
00:37:03,282 --> 00:37:07,013
Larry, Ruth, I can't tell you how much
I appreciate your support on this project.

537
00:37:07,186 --> 00:37:10,019
At least you're keeping
the community center.

538
00:37:10,189 --> 00:37:13,181
Unless you're willing to reconsider
the entire project.

539
00:37:13,359 --> 00:37:16,294
I'm afraid that won't happen.
It is over 50 million in profits.

540
00:37:16,462 --> 00:37:19,954
I think it's immoral that any human being
should acquire that much wealth.

541
00:37:20,132 --> 00:37:21,793
I don't know how you sleep at night.

542
00:37:21,968 --> 00:37:23,162
A machine that plays the ocean.

543
00:37:31,243 --> 00:37:35,976
I used to come up here all the time
when I was a kid. My special place.

544
00:37:38,317 --> 00:37:40,182
I had a small one-bedroom
on Park and 91st.

545
00:37:42,254 --> 00:37:44,484
That's so very <i>Oliver Twist</i>.

546
00:37:44,656 --> 00:37:48,217
Times were hard. But you know what?
We were happy.

547
00:37:49,761 --> 00:37:53,162
- Didn't have a view as good as this.
- It's great, isn't it?

548
00:37:53,332 --> 00:37:56,495
I used to take up some ice cream
and my Carole King tape...

549
00:37:56,668 --> 00:37:58,135
...and look at the neighborhood.

550
00:37:58,303 --> 00:38:01,898
It's amazing what you could see. At night,
the whole building went downstairs.

551
00:38:02,074 --> 00:38:05,168
The fathers stood on one corner.
The mothers stood on the other.

552
00:38:05,344 --> 00:38:08,677
Kids would just ride their bicycles around.

553
00:38:08,847 --> 00:38:11,338
As you can see, not much has changed.

554
00:38:11,650 --> 00:38:14,847
Mr. and Mrs. Goldfarb would be sitting
in the middle of the street...

555
00:38:15,020 --> 00:38:19,684
...saving a parking space for their children
who were coming next weekend.

556
00:38:21,026 --> 00:38:23,358
And you up here on your own.

557
00:38:24,096 --> 00:38:26,792
It's hard to find a quiet place
in Brooklyn to think.

558
00:38:28,033 --> 00:38:32,333
Or to replay whatever argument
I just had with my mother.

559
00:38:33,372 --> 00:38:34,930
Yes.

560
00:38:35,107 --> 00:38:37,098
Yeah, she's terrifying.

561
00:38:37,276 --> 00:38:40,370
I thought she was gonna kill me
and feed me to the poor.

562
00:38:40,545 --> 00:38:42,877
Yeah, she's a piece of work.

563
00:38:43,882 --> 00:38:48,216
But for better or worse, she's the voice
in my head pushing me to do better.

564
00:38:48,387 --> 00:38:52,380
Challenge the accepted wisdom. Never
settle for a B instead of an A on a test.

565
00:38:52,557 --> 00:38:53,717
You once got a B?

566
00:38:53,959 --> 00:38:56,826
- Hypothetically speaking.
- Right.

567
00:38:57,562 --> 00:39:03,398
Of course, no matter how hard I try,
I will never live up to her expectations.

568
00:39:04,569 --> 00:39:09,029
Well, there are worse things in life.
Like no one having any expectations.

569
00:39:18,417 --> 00:39:21,409
There's something amuck
with this sponge cake.

570
00:39:21,987 --> 00:39:23,921
Tofu.

571
00:39:37,669 --> 00:39:41,002
You're not concentrating.
This offends me.

572
00:39:41,173 --> 00:39:43,266
Yeah, I'm sorry, Ton.

573
00:39:43,442 --> 00:39:44,739
I lost Lucy.

574
00:39:47,012 --> 00:39:50,675
I just think it's a shame because I've
come to rely on her for everything.

575
00:39:50,849 --> 00:39:55,013
And I trust her completely,
and she's funny.

576
00:39:55,187 --> 00:39:57,451
Not deliberately, of course.

577
00:39:57,622 --> 00:40:00,113
Hey, you know, it's probably
for the best though.

578
00:40:00,292 --> 00:40:02,590
Oh, yeah? Why is that?

579
00:40:03,295 --> 00:40:06,594
Two things I know is chess and women.

580
00:40:07,866 --> 00:40:12,701
Chess, it has rules, pieces,
rooks, knights, bishops.

581
00:40:12,871 --> 00:40:16,705
They move in predictable patterns.
Somebody wins, somebody loses.

582
00:40:16,875 --> 00:40:20,311
But women, they don't have no rules, man.

583
00:40:20,479 --> 00:40:22,640
They move in unpredictable ways too.

584
00:40:22,814 --> 00:40:25,305
Nobody ever wins or loses
when it comes to women.

585
00:40:25,484 --> 00:40:28,817
You talk about your feelings
until your breath is sucked out your body.

586
00:40:29,821 --> 00:40:32,551
All men are pawns when it comes
to women.

587
00:40:32,724 --> 00:40:35,989
Especially a smart one like Lucy.
She's hard to control.

588
00:40:36,161 --> 00:40:39,619
And you know, the man has got
to be in control.

589
00:40:41,032 --> 00:40:42,556
Like with me.

590
00:40:42,734 --> 00:40:47,762
I come home. When I walk in,
I know my mama has dinner on the table.

591
00:40:49,241 --> 00:40:52,506
All right, so you're still living at home?

592
00:40:53,178 --> 00:40:55,169
Yeah. Yeah.

593
00:40:55,580 --> 00:40:57,241
Of course.

594
00:41:01,853 --> 00:41:04,947
Here's somebody interesting,
Polly St. Clair.

595
00:41:05,123 --> 00:41:09,583
Well, it's a terrific resume, Polly.

596
00:41:09,761 --> 00:41:11,490
Congratulations on the baby.

597
00:41:11,863 --> 00:41:12,921
What baby?

598
00:41:14,433 --> 00:41:17,266
Maybe you should check with me
before you talk.

599
00:41:17,436 --> 00:41:19,427
What baby?

600
00:41:22,207 --> 00:41:24,505
I'd like to talk about
your moot-court experience.

601
00:41:24,676 --> 00:41:25,768
What baby?

602
00:41:26,111 --> 00:41:28,204
Yeah, what baby?

603
00:41:34,152 --> 00:41:35,551
You should do the interviews on your own.

604
00:41:42,894 --> 00:41:45,089
Harry Raskin, Richard Beck.

605
00:41:47,165 --> 00:41:49,099
Interesting prospects for my replacement.
Let's see.

606
00:41:51,302 --> 00:41:52,564
No, it's gotta be a woman.

607
00:41:52,737 --> 00:41:53,897
What a surprise.

608
00:41:54,072 --> 00:41:57,701
I suppose a certain bust size would help.
Maybe some bathing-suit shots?

609
00:41:58,309 --> 00:42:01,301
It will annoy Howard if it's a woman.

610
00:42:01,479 --> 00:42:02,810
- Thank you.
- Tell you what.

611
00:42:02,981 --> 00:42:05,074
All I want is someone
as intelligent as you...

612
00:42:05,250 --> 00:42:07,309
...but a little less tense
and argumentative.

613
00:42:07,485 --> 00:42:10,579
A sort of Katharine Hepburn figure.

614
00:42:10,755 --> 00:42:12,484
You don't deserve Katharine Hepburn.

615
00:42:12,657 --> 00:42:14,090
- Audrey Hepburn.
- Also too good.

616
00:42:14,259 --> 00:42:16,159
Just stay away from the Hepburns.

617
00:42:16,327 --> 00:42:17,760
You forgot a beet.

618
00:42:17,929 --> 00:42:19,590
Beet.

619
00:42:20,265 --> 00:42:21,926
Thank you.

620
00:42:34,679 --> 00:42:36,943
I've got that charity tennis thing tonight.

621
00:42:37,115 --> 00:42:41,745
And I need to know, does this shirt make
me look a bit kind of Bjorn Borg?

622
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:46,118
Ansel and I got into a huge fight,
and I think we just broke up.

623
00:42:46,357 --> 00:42:47,346
Really?

624
00:42:47,525 --> 00:42:50,289
He wants me to go on a Greenpeace boat.

625
00:42:50,461 --> 00:42:52,292
He thinks I can't embrace life.

626
00:42:52,463 --> 00:42:54,863
Is that the case?
Because I just don't see it.

627
00:42:55,033 --> 00:42:56,557
I just don't see it.

628
00:42:56,868 --> 00:43:00,634
And by the way, how can I embrace him
when he is never here?

629
00:43:00,805 --> 00:43:06,266
Maybe it's me. Maybe the rose-colored
glasses have finally come off.

630
00:43:08,980 --> 00:43:10,379
Okay.

631
00:43:10,548 --> 00:43:13,483
We obviously can't leave you alone
with the stapler.

632
00:43:13,651 --> 00:43:16,279
I'll tell you what. I'll cancel tennis.

633
00:43:16,454 --> 00:43:19,651
They always make me play with Ed Koch.
What can we do to cheer you up?

634
00:43:19,824 --> 00:43:21,257
Nothing. There's no solution.

635
00:43:21,426 --> 00:43:22,791
Good. Good attitude.

636
00:43:22,961 --> 00:43:24,724
I can't help it if I don't like boats.

637
00:43:26,664 --> 00:43:28,131
Surely not all boats.

638
00:43:28,299 --> 00:43:31,166
Yes, all boats.

639
00:43:33,171 --> 00:43:36,663
I don't understand.
What is wrong with me?

640
00:43:36,841 --> 00:43:39,173
At the moment,
huge quantities of alcohol.

641
00:43:39,344 --> 00:43:42,074
I don't know. I just seem
to drive men away.

642
00:43:42,247 --> 00:43:44,181
There's Ansel.

643
00:43:44,349 --> 00:43:47,250
